                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5315/625.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Reid</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Reid says the foreign office has received a reply from the French Government
                    which is considered unsatisfactory and as demanding more than the English can
                    accede to, and that the foreign office has to-day telegraphed representative of
                    British group now negotiating in Paris to sacrifice in favor of French
                    sufficient mileage to make French and German sections equal in length. Adds that
                    it is hoped French foreign office will accept such a compromise.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
